		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You came to slay and will not be deterred. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Your Strength or Constitution score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can use your @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.9txksq0xfe5sgspl]{Furious Critical} feature with any weapon.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">While you are raging, your weapon&rsquo;s damage dice increase by one step (for example, a dagger would deal 1d6 points of damage and a greatsword would deal 2d8). If the weapon already deals a d12 of damage, it gains a flat +2 bonus instead.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Half your berserker levels count as fighter levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.7vvqy990w8pxatdy]{Indomitable} feature.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">When you activate your rage, you can let out a devastating roar, strike the ground or something similar. Creatures within 10 feet of you must make a Constitution save against your maneuver DC or take 4d4 points of thunder damage and be deafened for one minute. A creature that succeeds on its save takes half damage and is not deafened. A creature deafened this way can repeat the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on a success.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
